Caption:
```
EMAs aren't support/resistance. ðŸ“‰

They're trend filters.

Common MA mistakes:

âŒ "Price bounced off the 200 EMA" â€” No, it bounced near a level that happened to be there

âŒ "Golden Cross = Buy signal" â€” By the time it crosses, the move is often over

âŒ "EMA crossover strategy" â€” Lagging signals in ranging markets = death by 1000 cuts

How to actually use MAs:

âœ… Trend filter â€” Price above 200 EMA? Look for longs. Below? Look for shorts.

âœ… Multi-timeframe alignment â€” All MAs pointing same direction = strong trend

âœ… Context, not triggers â€” MAs describe trend, they don't predict reversals

