POST #26 â€” The Liquidity Lie: Liquidity Sweeps Deep Dive
â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•

ðŸ“˜ SOURCE
Type: ðŸŽ“ Education Hub Lesson (Deep Dive)
Angle: Liquidity Sweeps
URL: https://education.signalpilot.io/curriculum/beginner/01-the-liquidity-lie.html

â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
ð• TWITTER
â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€

Copy:
```
A liquidity sweep is not a breakdown.

Price breaks below support, grabs stops, and immediately reverses.

That's not "support failing." That's institutions filling orders.

Learn to recognize the difference.
```

Image: Chart showing liquidity sweep with annotation
Hashtags: #LiquiditySweep #SmartMoney #TradingEducation #SignalPilot

â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€
ðŸ“¸ INSTAGRAM
â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€

Caption:
```
A liquidity sweep is NOT a breakdown. ðŸŽ¯

What a sweep looks like:
â†’ Price breaks below support
â†’ Stops get triggered (retail sells)
â†’ Price IMMEDIATELY reverses back up
â†’ Institutions filled their buy orders

What a real breakdown looks like:
â†’ Price breaks below support
â†’ Retests support as resistance
â†’ Continues lower
â†’ No immediate reversal

The difference:

SWEEP = Quick wick below, fast reversal, trap
BREAKDOWN = Sustained move, retest, continuation

When you see price spike through a level and snap back â€” that's not failure.

That's hunting.

ðŸ”— Learn to recognize sweeps in bio.

.
.
.
