## POST 123 â€” ðŸ“ THE COMPOUND EFFECT IN TRADING (Blog)

**Source:** https://blog.signalpilot.io/articles/compound-effect-trading/

### ð• Twitter

**Copy:**
> 1% per day doesn't sound like much.
>
> But 1% compounded daily = 1,278% per year.
>
> Small, consistent gains beat occasional home runs.
>
> The compound effect is how traders become wealthy. Slowly, then suddenly.

**Image:** Compound growth curve showing exponential growth

**Hashtags:** #CompoundEffect #Compounding #TradingMath #SignalPilot #TradingEducation

---

### ðŸ“¸ Instagram

**Caption:**
> The Compound Effect in trading ðŸ“ˆ
>
> THE MATH:
> â—¾ 1% daily = 1,278% yearly (compounded)
> â—¾ 0.5% daily = 546% yearly
> â—¾ Even 0.25% daily = 152% yearly
>
> THE LESSON:
> You don't need home runs.
> You need consistency.
>
> HOME RUN TRADER:
> â—¾ Big wins, big losses
> â—¾ Emotional rollercoaster
> â—¾ Inconsistent results
>
> COMPOUND TRADER:
> â—¾ Small, consistent gains
> â—¾ Steady growth
> â—¾ Wealth over time
>
> Slow is smooth. Smooth is fast.
>
