## POST 173 â€” ðŸ“ THE SUNK COST FALLACY IN TRADING (Blog)

**Source:** https://blog.signalpilot.io/articles/sunk-cost-fallacy/

### ð• Twitter

**Copy:**
> "I've held this long, I can't sell now."
>
> That's the sunk cost fallacy.
>
> What you've lost doesn't matter.
> What happens next does.
>
> The market doesn't care about your entry price. Neither should you.

**Image:** Visual showing sunk cost trap vs rational exit

**Hashtags:** #SunkCostFallacy #TradingPsychology #TradingMistakes #SignalPilot #TradingEducation

---

### ðŸ“¸ Instagram

**Caption:**
> The Sunk Cost Fallacy ðŸª¤
>
> THE TRAP:
> "I've lost so much, I have to hold to break even"
>
> THE REALITY:
> â—¾ The market doesn't know your entry
> â—¾ Past losses don't determine future moves
> â—¾ Holding a loser ties up capital
> â—¾ Hope is not a strategy
>
> THE QUESTION TO ASK:
> "If I had no position, would I enter here?"
>
> If NO â†’ Exit. Take the loss.
> If YES â†’ Maybe hold. But be honest.
>
> YOUR ENTRY PRICE IS IRRELEVANT
> Only current structure matters.
>
> What happened doesn't matter.
> What happens next does.
>
> Full article in bio ðŸ”—

**Image:** 1080x1080 â€” Sunk cost trap visual with rational exit alternative

**Hashtags:** #SunkCostFallacy #TradingPsychology #TradingMistakes #HoldingLosers #SignalPilot #CryptoTrading #ForexTrading #TradingEducation #CutYourLosses #RationalTrading #LearnTrading #TradingMindset #BreakEvenTrap #EmotionalTrading #LetItGo

---

