---

### ð• Twitter

**Copy:**
> Fibonacci retracements: measuring pullbacks within trends.
>
> 38.2%, 50%, 61.8%, 78.6%
>
> These levels often act as support/resistance during corrections. Not magicâ€”just areas many traders watch.
>
> ðŸŽ“ [link]

**Image:** Chart showing Fibonacci retracement levels with price reactions

**Hashtags:** #Fibonacci #Retracements #SignalPilot #TradingEducation #TechnicalAnalysis

---

### ðŸ“¸ Instagram

**Caption:**
> ðŸ“ FIBONACCI RETRACEMENTS
>
> Measuring pullbacks within trends.
>
> ðŸ“Š KEY LEVELS:
>
> â†’ 23.6% â€” Shallow retracement
> â†’ 38.2% â€” Moderate retracement
> â†’ 50% â€” Half the move
> â†’ 61.8% â€” Golden ratio (most watched)
> â†’ 78.6% â€” Deep retracement
>
> ðŸŽ¯ HOW TO USE:
>
> 1. Identify a clear impulse move
> 2. Draw Fib from swing low to swing high (uptrend)
> 3. Or swing high to swing low (downtrend)
> 4. Watch for reactions at levels
>
> âœ¦ WHY IT WORKS:
>
> â†’ Self-fulfilling prophecy
> â†’ Many traders watch same levels
> â†’ Confluence with other factors
>
> âš ï¸ IMPORTANT:
>
> â†’ Fib levels aren't magic
> â†’ They're AREAS of interest
> â†’ Combine with structure, volume, etc.
>
> Free lesson ðŸŽ“ Link in bio
>
> âš ï¸ Educational only. Not financial advice.

