> Divergence: when price and an indicator disagree.
>
> Price makes new high, RSI doesn't = bearish divergence
> Price makes new low, RSI doesn't = bullish divergence
>
> Disagreement often precedes change.
>
> ðŸŽ“ [link]

**Image:** Chart showing bullish and bearish divergence with RSI

**Hashtags:** #Divergence #RSI #SignalPilot #TradingEducation #TechnicalAnalysis

---

### ðŸ“¸ Instagram

**Caption:**
> ðŸ”€ DIVERGENCE TRADING
>
> When price and momentum disagree, pay attention.
>
> ðŸ“‰ BEARISH DIVERGENCE:
>
> â†’ Price makes HIGHER high
> â†’ Indicator makes LOWER high
> â†’ Momentum weakening
> â†’ Potential reversal warning
>
> ðŸ“ˆ BULLISH DIVERGENCE:
>
> â†’ Price makes LOWER low
> â†’ Indicator makes HIGHER low
> â†’ Selling exhaustion
> â†’ Potential reversal warning
>
> ðŸŽ¯ COMMON INDICATORS FOR DIVERGENCE:
>
> â†’ RSI
> â†’ MACD
> â†’ Stochastic
> â†’ Volume (via Volume Oracle)
>
> âš ï¸ IMPORTANT NOTES:
>
> âœ¦ Divergence = warning, not signal
> âœ¦ Can persist before reversal
> âœ¦ Works best at key levels
> âœ¦ Confirm with structure break
>
> Divergence says "something may be changing." Your job: investigate.
>
