## POST 382 â€” ðŸŽ“ RECAP: CORRELATION IN TRADING

**Source:** `https://education.signalpilot.io/curriculum/intermediate/38-correlation.html`

---

### ð• Twitter

**Copy:**
> Correlation: when assets move together (or opposite).
>
> â†’ BTC and ETH: highly correlated
> â†’ USD and Gold: often inverse
>
> Understanding correlation helps diversify risk and avoid doubling exposure.
>
> ðŸŽ“ [link]

**Image:** Correlation matrix or two charts showing correlated assets

**Hashtags:** #Correlation #Diversification #SignalPilot #TradingEducation

---

### ðŸ“¸ Instagram

**Caption:**
> ðŸ”— CORRELATION IN TRADING
>
> How assets move relative to each other.
>
> ðŸ“Š CORRELATION TYPES:
>
> âž• POSITIVE CORRELATION (+1)
> â†’ Assets move in same direction
> â†’ BTC up â†’ ETH usually up
> â†’ Risk: doubled exposure
>
> âž– NEGATIVE CORRELATION (-1)
> â†’ Assets move opposite
> â†’ USD up â†’ Gold often down
> â†’ Useful for hedging
>
> 0ï¸âƒ£ NO CORRELATION (0)
> â†’ No relationship
> â†’ Independent movement
> â†’ True diversification
>
> ðŸŽ¯ WHY IT MATTERS:
>
> âœ¦ RISK MANAGEMENT
> â†’ Two correlated longs = 2x risk
> â†’ Think you're diversified but aren't
>
> âœ¦ HEDGING
> â†’ Negative correlation protects
> â†’ Offset potential losses
>
> âœ¦ CONFIRMATION
> â†’ Correlated assets confirming = stronger signal
>
> âš ï¸ NOTE: Correlations change over time!
>
> Free lesson ðŸŽ“ Link in bio
>
> âš ï¸ Educational only. Not financial advice.

**Image:** 1080x1080 â€” Correlation examples: positive (BTC/ETH), negative (USD/Gold), with charts

