> ðŸ“ˆ SMALL CONSISTENT WINS
>
> "Small consistent wins beat occasional big wins.
>
> Consistency compounds.
> Inconsistency crashes.
>
> Stack the small ones. The big picture takes care of itself."
>
> The math:
>
> ðŸ“Š TRADER A (Inconsistent)
> â†’ +50%, -40%, +30%, -45%
> â†’ Emotional rollercoaster
> â†’ Net: barely positive, stressed
>
> ðŸ“Š TRADER B (Consistent)
> â†’ +5%, +3%, +4%, +2%
> â†’ Boring, steady
> â†’ Net: compounding, calm
>
> Why small wins are better:
>
> âœ¦ PSYCHOLOGY
> â†’ Easier to execute
> â†’ Less emotional attachment
> â†’ Sustainable long-term
>
> âœ¦ MATHEMATICS
> â†’ Losing 50% requires 100% to recover
> â†’ Losing 5% requires ~5.3% to recover
> â†’ Small drawdowns = faster recovery
>
> âœ¦ COMPOUNDING
> â†’ Consistent small gains stack
> â†’ No devastating setbacks
>
> Boring builds wealth. Exciting destroys it.
>
> Save this ðŸ“Œ

