## POST 462 â€” ðŸŽ“ Liquidity Sweeps vs. Grabs

**Source:** `https://education.signalpilot.io/curriculum/advanced/64-liquidity-sweeps-grabs.html`

---

### ð• Twitter

**Copy:**
> Not all liquidity hunts are equal.
>
> Sweep: Quick wick, immediate reversal.
> Grab: Sustained move through liquidity, slower return.
>
> The speed of reaction often indicates intent.
>
> Understanding the difference adds nuance.
>
> Learn more â†’ [link]

**Image:** Chart comparing sweep (quick wick) vs. grab (sustained move)

**Hashtags:** #LiquiditySweep #LiquidityGrab #SmartMoney #SignalPilot #TradingEducation

---

### ðŸ“¸ Instagram

**Caption:**
> ðŸ’§ LIQUIDITY SWEEPS VS. GRABS
>
> Same concept. Different execution.
>
> LIQUIDITY SWEEP:
> â†’ Fast wick through level
> â†’ Immediate rejection
> â†’ Quick reversal
> â†’ Often single candle
> â†’ Shows aggressive response
>
> LIQUIDITY GRAB:
> â†’ Sustained push through level
> â†’ Multiple candles beyond
> â†’ Slower return
> â†’ Absorption phase visible
> â†’ Shows gradual accumulation/distribution
>
> WHY IT MATTERS:
> â†’ Sweeps suggest urgency
> â†’ Grabs suggest patience
> â†’ Different trading responses needed
> â†’ Context determines which to expect
>
> Same liquidity hunt. Different character.
>
