---

### ðŸ“¸ Instagram

**Caption:**
> ðŸ“ RISK-ADJUSTED RETURNS
>
> Not all returns are created equal.
>
> THE PROBLEM WITH RAW RETURNS:
> â†’ 20% return sounds good
> â†’ But what was the risk?
> â†’ What was the drawdown?
> â†’ How bumpy was the ride?
>
> KEY METRICS:
>
> ðŸ“Š SHARPE RATIO
> â†’ Return per unit of risk
> â†’ Higher = better risk-adjusted
> â†’ Above 1.0 is generally good
>
> ðŸ“Š SORTINO RATIO
> â†’ Like Sharpe, but only downside
> â†’ Penalizes bad volatility
> â†’ More relevant for traders
>
> ðŸ“Š MAX DRAWDOWN
> â†’ Largest peak-to-trough loss
> â†’ Can you survive it?
> â†’ Emotional and capital test
>
> THE COMPARISON:
> â†’ Strategy A: 20% return, 50% drawdown
> â†’ Strategy B: 15% return, 10% drawdown
> â†’ B is often better despite lower return
>
> Quality of returns matters.
>
> ðŸŽ“ Full lesson in curriculum
