## POST 522 â€” ðŸŽ“ Correlation in Trading

**Source:** `https://education.signalpilot.io/curriculum/intermediate/35-correlation-trading.html`

---

### ð• Twitter

**Copy:**
> Correlation: when assets move together (or opposite).
>
> Understanding correlation helps:
> â†’ Diversify properly
> â†’ Avoid doubled risk
> â†’ Find confirmation
>
> Trading BTC and ETH together? That's not diversification.
>
> Learn correlation basics â†’ [link]

**Image:** Correlation chart showing positively and negatively correlated assets

**Hashtags:** #Correlation #Diversification #SignalPilot #TradingEducation #RiskManagement

---

### ðŸ“¸ Instagram

**Caption:**
> ðŸ”— CORRELATION IN TRADING
>
> How assets move together matters.
>
> TYPES OF CORRELATION:
>
> âž• POSITIVE CORRELATION
> â†’ Assets move in same direction
> â†’ BTC & ETH (often)
> â†’ EUR/USD & GBP/USD (often)
>
> âž– NEGATIVE CORRELATION
> â†’ Assets move opposite
> â†’ USD & Gold (sometimes)
> â†’ Risk-on vs. Risk-off assets
>
> 0ï¸âƒ£ NO CORRELATION
> â†’ Independent movement
> â†’ True diversification
>
> WHY IT MATTERS:
>
> âš ï¸ HIDDEN RISK
> â†’ Long BTC + Long ETH = doubled crypto risk
> â†’ Feels diversified, isn't really
>
> âœ… PROPER DIVERSIFICATION
> â†’ Uncorrelated or negatively correlated assets
> â†’ Actual risk reduction
>
> âœ… CONFIRMATION
> â†’ Correlated asset confirming move
> â†’ Adds confidence
>
> Know what moves with what.
>
> ðŸŽ“ Full lesson in curriculum
>
> ðŸ”— Link in bio

**Image:** 1080x1080 â€” Two charts side by side showing correlated movement, correlation coefficient displayed

