## POST 552 â€” ðŸŽ“ Candlestick Psychology

**Source:** `https://education.signalpilot.io/curriculum/intermediate/44-candlestick-psychology.html`

---

### ð• Twitter

**Copy:**
> Every candle tells a story of battle.
>
> The body: who won (buyers or sellers)
> The wicks: who tried and failed
> The size: intensity of the fight
>
> Read candles as psychology, not just patterns.
>
> Learn candle psychology â†’ [link]

**Image:** Candlestick anatomy with psychological meaning annotated

**Hashtags:** #CandlestickPsychology #PriceAction #SignalPilot #TradingEducation #CandleReading

---

### ðŸ“¸ Instagram

**Caption:**
> ðŸ•¯ï¸ CANDLESTICK PSYCHOLOGY
>
> Every candle is a story.
>
> ANATOMY OF A CANDLE:
>
> ðŸ“Š THE BODY
> â†’ Distance between open and close
> â†’ Shows who won the session
> â†’ Green/white = buyers won
> â†’ Red/black = sellers won
>
> ðŸ“ THE WICKS
> â†’ Price that was rejected
> â†’ Upper wick = sellers pushed back
> â†’ Lower wick = buyers pushed back
>
> ðŸ“ THE SIZE
> â†’ Large body = strong conviction
> â†’ Small body = indecision
> â†’ Long wicks = rejection
>
> PSYCHOLOGICAL READS:
>
> ðŸ”¨ HAMMER (long lower wick)
> â†’ Sellers tried, buyers overwhelmed
> â†’ Potential reversal
>
> â­ DOJI (tiny body, equal wicks)
> â†’ Neither side won
> â†’ Indecision, potential turning point
>
> ðŸ“ˆ MARUBOZU (full body, no wicks)
> â†’ Complete dominance
> â†’ Strong conviction
>
> Read the story, not just the shape.
>
> ðŸŽ“ Full lesson in curriculum
>
> ðŸ”— Link in bio

